The Eastern Conscience, a socio-cultural organization, has expressed its support for Mallam Abba Kyari, the Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari and Mamman Daura, a cousin of Mr President. The convener of the organisation, Evang. Myke Ikoku, said yesterday in a message that the ‘arranged’ protests held a few days ago by ‘some disgruntled persons’ was to discredit them. According to him, it is a known fact that every political victory is built on the back of sacrifices of a few and that it is only expected that for the sake of stability, loyalty and the much needed support a leader requires those who have struggled with him through thick and thin ought to be there to manage the success. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “This management of the success of Mr. President’s victory has to be in the hands of these two very capable hands along with others who are part of the kitchen cabinet and brainbox of this administration.” Protesters march to villa, back Kyari, Daura, others Remembering a rare gem called Ciroma Daura, ex-DSS boss will not return Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin